data.reasoningText:
The issue is that the `Create_Post_InvalidModelState_ReturnsView` test creates an Instructor without initializing `CourseAssignments`, and then `PopulateAssignedCourseData` tries to access `instructor.CourseAssignments.Select(c => c.CourseID)` which is null.

Looking at the code:
```csharp
private void PopulateAssignedCourseData(Instructor instructor)
{
    var allCourses = db.Courses;
    var instructorCourses = new HashSet<int>(instructor.CourseAssignments.Select(c => c.CourseID));


```

If `instructor.CourseAssignments` is null, this throws a NullReferenceException. The solution is to ensure the test initializes the `CourseAssignments` collection on the instructor object before passing it to the method.

